POST -> http://localhost:8080/orders

TEST SUCCESS MESSAGE
====================
{
  "orderId": "ORD-1001",
  "customerName": "Venkat",
  "product": "Laptop",
  "amount": 2000
}

TEST FAILURE MESSAGE
====================

{
  "orderId": "ORD-9999",
  "customerName": "Venkat",
  "product": "MacBook",
  "amount": 90000
}


1. Idempotent Producer

enable.idempotence: true

Avoid duplicate messages during retries.

2. Async Publishing

kafkaTemplate.send(...).whenComplete(...)

Non-blocking message publishing.

Producer does NOT wait for Kafka response.

Benefits: high throughput, better performance, scalable publishing

3. Message Keys

.setHeader(KafkaHeaders.KEY, orderId)

Ensure same key goes to same partition.

4. Compression

compression-type: snappy

Reduce network traffic.

Benefits: faster transfer, lower bandwidth, better throughput

5. Batching

batch-size: 32768
linger.ms: 10

Producer groups multiple messages into one batch.

Benefits: fewer network calls, better throughput, improved performance

6. Retries

retries: 5

Retry temporary failures automatically.


7. Acknowledgments

acks: all

Strong durability guarantee.

Kafka waits until replicas confirm write.

Benefit: Avoid message loss.


